{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f0dd22d4-1906-481b-8da6-28655ef9929b","content":"Here's the recommended setup:\n\n## 1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`) — minimal with MSTest.Sdk\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\n`MSTest.Sdk` replaces the usual `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` and auto-includes all MSTest packages, `Microsoft.Testing.Platform`, and the runner — no extra `<PackageReference>` items needed.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution — `.runsettings`\n\nCreate a `*.runsettings` file (e.g. `my.runsettings`) at the repo root:\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\" ?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <Parallelize>\n      <Workers>0</Workers>              <!-- 0 = use all logical processors -->\n      <Scope>ClassLevel</Scope>         <!-- or MethodLevel for max parallelism -->\n    </Parallelize>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\nAlternatively, skip the `.runsettings` file and use an assembly-level attribute in a file like `AssemblyInfo.cs`:\n\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Workers = 0, Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]\n```\n\n## 3. Run database tests sequentially\n\nMark your database test class with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting;\n\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]                        // ← runs sequentially, outside parallel pool\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Can_Insert_And_Read_Back()\n    {\n        // ...\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task Transactions_Roll_Back_On_Failure()\n    {\n        // ...\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n| Concept | Mechanism |\n|---|---|\n| **Parallel by default** | `[assembly: Parallelize]` or `<Parallelize>` in `.runsettings` |\n| **Opt-out specific classes** | `[DoNotParallelize]` on the class |\n| **Opt-out a single method** | `[DoNotParallelize]` on the method |\n| **`Workers = 0`** | Uses all available CPUs |\n| **`ClassLevel` scope** | Methods within one class run serially; different classes run in parallel |\n| **`MethodLevel` scope** | Maximum parallelism — every method can run concurrently |\n\nFor database tests, `ClassLevel` scope + `[DoNotParallelize]` is the safest combo — it keeps those tests fully sequential while everything else runs in parallel.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"26a69a49-1205-4a81-b373-be506468439e","outputTokens":703,"requestId":"602D:3F1DAE:2555BEE:27F862A:6A031286"},"id":"594ed116-50a9-4405-bc91-935f68c7ee36","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:44:25.248Z","parentId":"5631bf99-638e-4d5b-89a3-ddbff754ccbc"}
